          <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">approximately</NUMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$110 billion</NUMEX>, implying a net economic
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">savings</ENAMEX> (including the cost of insulation) on the order
          of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$80 billion</NUMEX>.
          When economic values are assigned to the mortality and
          morbidity outcomes as described above, the environmental
          externalities averted through increased insulation amount
          to <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">approximately $1.3 billion</NUMEX> per year. Over <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">99%</NUMEX> of this
          total is related to premature mortality, indicating that
